HEADWORD: Quirinal
<hw>Quir"i*nal</hw> <pr>(kw⟦icr⟧r"⟦icr⟧*n⟦ait⟧l <it>or</it>
kw⟦icr⟧`r⟦imac⟧"n⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Quirinalis</ets>, fr. <ets>Quirinus</ets>, a name of
Romulus.]</ety> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, the hill
<xex>Collis Quirinalis</xex>, now <xex>Monte Quirinale</xex> (one of the
seven hills of Rome), or a modern royal place situated upon it. Also
used substantively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

